{{see|Spleen}}

==English==
===Etymology===
From the Old French ''[[esplen]]'', from Latin ''[[splen|spl&#275;n]]'', from Greek [[σπλήν]] ([[milt]]).

===Pronunciation===
*splēn, /spliːn/, /<tt>spli:n</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-iːn|Rhymes: -iːn]]

===Noun===
'''spleen''' (''plural:'' '''spleens''')

# {{anatomy}} In [[vertebrate]]s, including [[human]]s, a ductless vascular gland, located in the left upper abdomen near the stomach. It destroys old [[red blood cell]]s, removes debris from the [[bloodstream]], acts as a reservoir of blood, and produces [[lymphocyte]]s.
#(''archaic, except in the [[set phrase]] ''"to [[vent#Transitive verb|vent]] one’s spleen") A bad [[mood]]; [[spite]]fulness.

